{"key":"post-11085662","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11085662</id>\n<content>Not only is it not hooked up right, it can't be hooked up right even if you bought an outlet.&amp;nbsp; A switch is in SERIES with the line to the device.&amp;nbsp; It doesn't have the rest of the wires there, unless the switch is fed first, which is rare.&amp;nbsp; Usually they run power to the light box on the ceiling, and then drop a wire to the switch.&amp;nbsp; If there's only one cable entering the light switch box, that's what they did.&amp;nbsp; You can't convert that to an outlet.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If all you have is a closet light and switch, simply get one of those outlets that screw into a light bulb socket.&amp;nbsp; It will be hot when the switch is turned on.&amp;nbsp; That is, if those damn things are still legal.&amp;nbsp; They don't have a ground connection.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11085943</next>\n<prev>11084823</prev>\n<first>11083973</first>\n<last>11086126</last>\n<when>1253324895</when>\n<utime>09/19/09 04:48 AM</utime>\n</post>"}